## Phase Semantics

### Phase 1 — Dummy Test (sandbox)
- Executed by VPS Bridge + n8n-as-code-service on Aivory's sandbox.
- Agent simulates dry-run reasoning and produces test result JSON (see `SKILL.md`).
- Agent must not execute the test itself.
- On failure: agent suggests repair (see Repair Policy). VPS Bridge re-runs. Max 3 attempts.
- After test (pass or fail): n8n-as-code-service unpublishes and deletes the dummy workflow.

### Phase 2 — User Confirmation
- Frontend shows workflow preview + setup report.
- Agent explains workflow in business language, node by node.
- User must explicitly confirm before anything is applied.
- Never imply the workflow is deployed at this stage.

### Phase 3 — Activation
- Activate popup collects the user's own n8n host URL and API key.
- Key is pass-through only — never stored, never echoed.
- Deployment goes through VPS Bridge only.
- Agent tells user to proceed through the Activate flow — agent does not trigger deployment.

